[~ethomas], fix looks good to me.

Rather than having three separate log statements:

{code}
      LOG.info("Error creating resource " + resourceId);
      LOG.error(ex);
      LOG.debug(ex, ex);
{code}

you could use something like:

{code}
      LOG.error( "Error creating resource ${resourceId}: ${ex}", LOG.debugEnabled ? ex : null )
{code}

which would put the context (resourceId) next to the error it relates to.
